body:
#### Issue details
InputProcessor removing itself from an InputMultiplexer causes exception.

InputMultiplexer currently caches length before iterating
```java
for (int i = 0, n = processors.size; i < n; i++)
```

Not caching, will prevent the crash but will drop input to one InputProcesser on the frame one is removed.

```java
for (int i = 0; i < processors.size; i++)
```

Another fix might be to only actually process the removal after input is done for a frame.

Or this can just be an expected behavior and documented to inform users to wrap removals invoked from input in a postRunnable.

This issue also occurs when adding a listener to the front of the listeners from a listener's callback. This will not crash, but will cause the last listener to not receive input. As well as cause the immediately following listener to be triggered a second time (if it is not last).

#### Reproduction steps/code
```java
import com.badlogic.gdx.*;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication;

public class InputMultiplexerRemoveTest extends ApplicationAdapter {
	InputMultiplexer multiplexer;
	InputTestProcessor processor1;
	InputTestProcessor processor2;
	
	@Override
	public void create () {
		multiplexer = new InputMultiplexer();

		processor1 = new InputTestProcessor();
		processor2 = new InputTestProcessor();
		multiplexer.addProcessor(processor1);
		multiplexer.addProcessor(processor2);
		
		Gdx.input.setInputProcessor(multiplexer);
	}

	public static void main (String[] args) throws Exception {
		new LwjglApplication(new InputMultiplexerRemoveTest());
	}
	
	class InputTestProcessor extends InputAdapter
	{
		@Override
		public boolean keyDown (int keycode) {
			if(this == processor1) {
				multiplexer.removeProcessor(processor1);
			}
			return false;
		}
	}
}
```

#### Version of LibGDX and/or relevant dependencies
1.9.9-SNAPSHOT

#### Stacktrace
```java
Exception in thread "LWJGL Application" java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException: index can't be >= size: 1 >= 1
	at com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Array.get(Array.java:154)
	at com.badlogic.gdx.InputMultiplexer.keyDown(InputMultiplexer.java:72)
	at com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglInput.processEvents(LwjglInput.java:317)
	at com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication.mainLoop(LwjglApplication.java:217)
	at com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication$1.run(LwjglApplication.java:126)
```

#### Please select the affected platforms
- [x] Android
- [ ] iOS (robovm)
- [ ] iOS (MOE)
- [ ] HTML/GWT
- [x] Windows
- [x] Linux
- [x] MacOS
